-- Copper Heads for Third Weekly Drop as China Takes Steps to Curb Inflation
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-11-26T01:07:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-26/copper-heads-for-third-weekly-drop-as-china-takes-steps-to-curb-inflation.html
Copper in London dropped as much as
0.5 percent to $8,300 a metric ton today and is poised for a
third weekly decline. The three-month contract on the London
Metal Exchange traded at $8,301 a ton by 9:03 a.m. in Shanghai.  March-delivery copper on the Shanghai Futures Exchange
gained 0.9 percent to 62,640 yuan a ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
